<h1><u>Speed Distance Time Calculators</u></h1>

</center>
<p>
Generic browser based speed, distance and time calculators written in javas=
cript by=20
<a href=3D"http://www.machinehead-software.co.uk/nigel_jones/index.html#mac=
hinehead_software_web_designers_developers_and_clones">Nigel Jones</a> for =
performance oriented cyclists and other racers.
</p>

<p>
If you can run Windows applications you might prefer a <a href=3D"http://ww=
w.machinehead-software.co.uk/bike/gears/speed_distance_time_calc.html">nice=
r and more compact version of these calculators</a> that ships with my <a h=
ref=3D"http://www.machinehead-software.co.uk/bike/gears/gear_calculator.htm=
l">bike gear calculator</a> or the additional functionality of my <a href=
=3D"http://www.machinehead-software.co.uk/bike/power/bicycle_power_calculat=
or.html">power calculator</a>.=20


Better still if your sport does involve bicycles my <a href=3D"http://www.m=
achinehead-software.co.uk/bike/gears/fixed_wheel_gear_calculator.html">fixe=
d wheel gear calculator</a> does some very similar calculations in a manner=
 that is more comprehensive because it does take your bicycle gearing and c=
adence into account but is obviously more complex as a result.=20
</p>
<p>
If you can't run windows applications, and/or your sport doesn't involve bi=
cycles so the additional functionality of <a href=3D"http://www.machinehead=
-software.co.uk/bike/gears/gear_calculator.html">GearCalc</a> and=20
<a href=3D"http://www.machinehead-software.co.uk/bike/power/bicycle_power_c=
alculator.html">PowerCalc</a> isn't of interest to you use these for free.=
=20
</p>





